          <td><span class="comp-good">None</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Shipping & Logistics</td>
          <td><span class="comp-bad">Complex, expensive</span></td>
          <td><span class="comp-good">Instant delivery</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Profit Margins</td>
          <td><span class="comp-bad">20–50% typical</span></td>
          <td><span class="comp-good">70–95% typical</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Scalability</td>
          <td><span class="comp-bad">Linear — more units = more cost</span></td>
          <td><span class="comp-good">Infinite — zero marginal cost</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Geographic Reach</td>
          <td><span class="comp-bad">Limited by shipping</span></td>
          <td><span class="comp-good">Global, instant</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Time to Market</td>
          <td><span class="comp-bad">Weeks to months</span></td>
          <td><span class="comp-good">Days to weeks</span></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── 5 BUYING TRIGGERS ── -->
<section class="triggers-section">
  <div class="section-label">Chapter 4 · Buyer Psychology</div>
  <h2 class="section-h">The Five Triggers That<br><em>Drive Every Purchase</em></h2>
  <p class="section-body">Behavioral science reveals the psychological levers behind every digital product sale. Understanding these is more valuable than any copywriting formula.</p>

  <div class="triggers-grid">
    <div class="trigger-card">
      <div class="trig-num">1</div>
      <div class="trig-name">Pain Avoidance</div>
      <div class="trig-desc">People pay more to avoid pain than to gain pleasure. Frame your product as escape from a specific, urgent suffering — not as a feature list.</div>
      <div class="trig-science">Nobel Prize · Kahneman Loss Aversion</div>
    </div>
    <div class="trigger-card">
      <div class="trig-num">2</div>
      <div class="trig-name">Time Compression</div>
      <div class="trig-desc">Modern buyers are time-starved. Quantify the hours your product saves. "Saves you 20 hours of design work" outsells any benefit statement.</div>
      <div class="trig-science">Premium for efficiency · Templates & swipe files</div>
    </div>
    <div class="trigger-card">
      <div class="trig-num">3</div>
      <div class="trig-name">Identity &amp; Aspiration</div>
      <div class="trig-desc">People buy the person they want to become. A fitness planner isn't about tracking — it represents the disciplined, healthy self the buyer aspires to be.</div>
      <div class="trig-science">Identity transformation · Not information</div>
    </div>
    <div class="trigger-card">
      <div class="trig-num">4</div>
      <div class="trig-name">Social Proof</div>
      <div class="trig-desc">When people see others have purchased and benefited, resistance drops dramatically. Testimonials are your single most powerful conversion tool.</div>
      <div class="trig-science">Cialdini · 6 Principles of Persuasion</div>
    </div>
    <div class="trigger-card">
      <div class="trig-num">5</div>
      <div class="trig-name">Scarcity &amp; Urgency</div>
      <div class="trig-desc">Limited-time pricing helps people overcome procrastination. Not manipulation — a legitimate strategy. The key is authenticity: never fake scarcity.</div>
      <div class="trig-science">Early-bird pricing · Launch windows</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── VALUE FORMULA ── -->
<section class="formula-section">
  <div class="formula-inner">
    <div class="formula-label">Chapter 4 · Value Perception Formula</div>
    <div class="formula-display">
      Perceived Value &nbsp;=&nbsp;
      <span class="frac">
        <span class="frac-top"><span class="gold-term">Dream Outcome</span> &times; <span class="gold-term">Likelihood of Success</span></span>
        <span class="frac-bot">Time Delay &times; Effort Required</span>
      </span>
    </div>
    <div class="formula-levers">
      <div class="fl-item">
        <div class="fl-action">↑ Increase</div>
        <div class="fl-text"><strong style="color:var(--text)">Dream Outcome</strong> — Make the promise bigger, more specific, more emotionally resonant.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="fl-item">
        <div class="fl-action">↑ Increase</div>
        <div class="fl-text"><strong style="color:var(--text)">Perceived Likelihood</strong> — Add testimonials, guarantees, case studies, and credentials.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="fl-item">
        <div class="fl-action">↓ Decrease</div>
        <div class="fl-text"><strong style="color:var(--text)">Time Delay</strong> — Promise faster results. "In 30 days" beats "eventually." Speed sells.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="fl-item">
        <div class="fl-action">↓ Decrease</div>
        <div class="fl-text"><strong style="color:var(--text)">Effort Required</strong> — Add done-for-you elements, templates, and simplification. Easy sells.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── PRICING ── -->
<section style="border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);">
  <div class="pricing-section">
    <div>
      <div class="section-label">Chapter 6 · Pricing Science</div>
      <h2 class="section-h">Pricing Is<br><em>Psychology</em></h2>
      <p class="section-body">A counterintuitive truth: raising your price often increases sales. When buyers can't evaluate quality before purchase — which is always true with digital products — they use price as a quality signal.</p>
      <div class="pricing-principles">
        <div class="pp-item">
          <div class="pp-name">Charm Pricing</div>
          <div class="pp-desc">$97 outsells $100. The left-digit effect makes the first number disproportionately important. Use prices ending in 7 or 9 for all digital products.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-item">
          <div class="pp-name">Anchoring</div>
          <div class="pp-desc">Present a higher reference price first. Show what private coaching costs ($997) before revealing your course at $197. The anchor shapes every subsequent judgment.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-item">
          <div class="pp-name">The Decoy Effect</div>
          <div class="pp-desc">The middle tier exists to be chosen. The top tier makes it look reasonable. The bottom tier pushes buyers upward. Three tiers always outperform one.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-item">
          <div class="pp-name">Price-Quality Inference</div>
          <div class="pp-desc">A $7 ebook signals low quality. A $47 ebook signals comprehensive, professional expertise. New creators almost always underprice — and it costs them trust.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="tier-label">The Three-Tier Model</div>
      <div class="pricing-tiers">
        <div class="tier-card">
          <div class="tier-badge">BASIC</div>
          <div class="tier-name">Core Product</div>
          <div class="tier-desc">The product alone, no extras. Serves price-sensitive buyers and creates a low-friction entry point into your ecosystem.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tier-card featured">
          <div class="tier-badge">✦ STANDARD — Best Value</div>
          <div class="tier-name">Core + Bonuses + Community</div>
          <div class="tier-desc">Core product plus worksheets, bonus materials, and community access. Label this your recommended option. Most buyers choose this tier.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tier-card">
          <div class="tier-badge">PREMIUM</div>
          <div class="tier-name">Everything + Personal Access</div>
          <div class="tier-desc">Standard plus personal feedback, live sessions, or direct coaching. Serves high-value buyers and makes Standard look like a bargain.</div>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 24px; padding: 20px; background: var(--gold-dim); border: 1px solid rgba(201,146,42,0.2); font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6;">
          <span style="color:var(--gold); font-family:'Space Mono',monospace; font-size:9px; letter-spacing:0.15em; display:block; margin-bottom:8px;">LAUNCH STRATEGY</span>
          Start 40–50% below your target price. After 50–100 sales, raise to standard. After 200+ reviews, raise to premium. Always grandfather existing customers.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── FUNNEL ── -->
<section class="funnel-section">
  <div class="funnel-inner">
    <div class="section-label">Chapter 10 · Automated Sales Funnels</div>
    <h2 class="section-h">The Evergreen Machine<br><em>That Sells While You Sleep</em></h2>
    <p class="section-body">A properly built funnel converts strangers into buyers automatically — 24 hours a day. The key insight most people miss: never try to go from discovery directly to sale. You must earn trust first.</p>

    <div class="funnel-stages">
