<!-- ── FATAL MISTAKES ── -->
<section class="mistakes-section">
  <div class="mistakes-inner">
    <div class="section-label">Chapter 12 · What Kills Digital Businesses</div>
    <h2 class="section-h">Ten Fatal Mistakes<br><em>and How to Avoid Them</em></h2>
    <div class="mistakes-grid">
      <div class="mistake-card">
        <div class="mk-num">MISTAKE 01</div>
        <div class="mk-name">Building Before Validating</div>
        <div class="mk-desc">The graveyard of digital products is full of beautifully designed courses nobody wanted. Pre-sell first. If people won't pay for a promise, they won't pay for a product.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="mistake-card">
        <div class="mk-num">MISTAKE 02</div>
        <div class="mk-name">Underpricing</div>
        <div class="mk-desc">A $5 ebook signals low quality, attracts bargain hunters, and requires massive volume for meaningful income. Price based on transformation value, not page count.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="mistake-card">
        <div class="mk-num">MISTAKE 03</div>
        <div class="mk-name">Ignoring Email Marketing</div>
        <div class="mk-desc">Social media followers are rented. Email subscribers are owned. Instagram can change its algorithm overnight. Your email list is the only asset you fully control.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="mistake-card">
        <div class="mk-num">MISTAKE 04</div>
        <div class="mk-name">Perfectionism</div>
        <div class="mk-desc">Waiting until your product is perfect is procrastination in disguise. Version two is always better than version one — but only if version one exists.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="mistake-card">
        <div class="mk-num">MISTAKE 05</div>
        <div class="mk-name">Selling Features, Not Outcomes</div>
        <div class="mk-desc">Nobody cares about 47 videos and 12 worksheets. They care about budgeting with confidence, losing 20 pounds, or starting a profitable side business. Always lead with the transformation.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="mistake-card">
        <div class="mk-num">MISTAKE 06</div>
        <div class="mk-name">One-and-Done Launching</div>
        <div class="mk-desc">A single launch is not a business strategy. People need to see your offer 5–7 times before taking action. Build evergreen systems that sell daily, not just launch week.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="mistake-card">
        <div class="mk-num">MISTAKE 07</div>
        <div class="mk-name">Not Collecting Testimonials</div>
        <div class="mk-desc">Every satisfied customer is a potential testimonial. Ask proactively. Send a specific question, not a vague request. Testimonials are the most effective sales tool in digital commerce.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="mistake-card">
        <div class="mk-num">MISTAKE 08</div>
        <div class="mk-name">Quitting Too Early</div>
        <div class="mk-desc">Most digital product businesses take 3–6 months of consistent effort before significant revenue. The first few months are not a verdict — they're the tuition you pay to build something real.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

